<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT and BEARINGS, CAMSHAFT and BUSHINGS -
        Installation - Crankshaft
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26508.3.4" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Crankshaft</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure the crankshaft has been inspected per instructions in this section before proceeding.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a lint-free cloth to wipe the crankcase bearing supports free of oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each bearing. Replace scored, chipped or worn bearings.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When inserting main bearings, make sure oil is not between the back side of the bearing and the
                    crankcase bearing saddles.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place upper main bearings in the crankcase. Make sure locking tabs on bearings are snapped
                in the crankcase saddle and oil holes in bearings line up with oil holes in crankcase.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Crankshaft thrust bearing is installed at the number 4 upper main bearing journal.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650835" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0717.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Upper main bearings lubrication</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate bearings with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650836" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd03/D0309.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft timing tool installed</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft timing tool</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft index mark</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install Crankshaft Timing Tool so index mark on camshaft gear is visible between alignment
                slot of the crankshaft timing tool.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a correct size lifting sling and hoist with a safety
                    latch on hook.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650837" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0710.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Lifting sling</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lifting sling</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a bolt in each end of the crankshaft (if removed). Attach hoist and lifting sling
                around crankshaft bolts and carefully lower it on the five main bearings.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
